<h1>About the Data Sources</h1>

<h2>List of Coins Dataset</h2>
<p>
  <strong>Description:</strong> This dataset provides a comprehensive list of cryptocurrencies with basic information about each coin, such as its name, symbol, and an identifier used for fetching more detailed data.
</p>
<p>
  <strong>Structure:</strong>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>name:</strong> The name of the cryptocurrency (e.g., Bitcoin).</li>
    <li><strong>symbol:</strong> The ticker symbol of the cryptocurrency (e.g., BTC).</li>
    <li><strong>id:</strong> A unique identifier for the cryptocurrency, used to fetch more details or historical data.</li>
  </ul>
</p>
<p>
  <strong>Database Tables and Columns:</strong>
  <ul>
    <li>Table Name: coins</li>
    <li>Columns:
      <ul>
        <li>id (primary key)</li>
        <li>name (string)</li>
        <li>symbol (string)</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>
</p>

<h2>Coin Details</h2>
<p>
  <strong>Description:</strong> Detailed information about a specific cryptocurrency, including its current price, market cap, circulating supply, and a brief description.
</p>
<p>
  <strong>Structure:</strong>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>id:</strong> Unique identifier for the cryptocurrency.</li>
    <li><strong>price:</strong> Current price of the cryptocurrency.</li>
    <li><strong>market_cap:</strong> Total market capitalization.</li>
    <li><strong>circulating_supply:</strong> The amount of the cryptocurrency that is currently in circulation.</li>
    <li><strong>description:</strong> A brief description of the cryptocurrency.</li>
  </ul>
</p>
<p>
  <strong>Database Table and Columns:</strong>
  <ul>
    <li>price (decimal)</li>
    <li>market_cap (decimal)</li>
    <li>circulating_supply (bigint)</li>
    <li>description (text)</li>
  </ul>
</p>

<p>
Integration and Relationships:
The datasets will be integrated primarily through the id (or coin_id in some tables) column, which acts as a foreign key linking the coins table with its details, current prices. This relational structure allows for efficient queries across different aspects of each coin, enabling detailed reporting, time-based price analyses, and the ability to search and visualize the evolution of cryptocurrency metrics over time. 
This integrated approach supports a flexible and comprehensive analysis platform, where users can explore cryptocurrencies from high-level overviews down to minute historical details.
 
</p>

